    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-06-02T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-06-02T00:00:00-05:00" n="1584"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1584">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.62/62.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">German Ambassador</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 1013.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-06-02">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 2, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Excellency</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the
                    receipt of your Embassy’s note of May 27th, in which it is requested that the
                    American naval vessels in Mexican west coast waters be directed to assume the
                    protection of German interests during the absence of H. M. S. <hi rend="italic"
                        >Nümberg</hi>.</p>
                <p>In reply I have the honor to inform your excellency that the Secretary of the
                    Navy informed this Department in a letter under date of May 29, 1914, that the
                    Commander in Chief of the Pacific Fleet has been given instructions in the sense
                    above indicated.</p>
                <p>Accept [etc.]</p>
                <closer>For the Secretary of State: <lb/>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Robert Lansing</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
